          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search          Prisoners' Union (Russian: Союз заключённых) is Russian human rights monitoring non-governmental organization. The organization was founded in 2008. Prisoners' Union foundation meeting was held in Moscow and was attended by 40 former political prisoners.[1][2][3] Prisoners' Union works to expose human rights violations within the penal system in Russia. Prisoners' Union publishes monitoring materials of situation in Russian prisons and holds press-conferences. Organization calls for an amnesty for all political prisoners in Russia.[4][5] See also[edit]  Prison abolition movement Prisoners' rights Human rights in Russia  References[edit]   ^ Москва. Съезд политзаключенных объявил о создании в России Союза заключенных ^ В Москве прошел съезд политзаключенных ^ Участники съезда политзаключенных решили создать Союз заключенных ^ Союз заключенных России предлагает провести амнистию ^ Требования Союза Заключенных   External links[edit]  Prisoners' Union - official website      This Russia-related article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e                         Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Prisoners%27_Union&oldid=715150253"          Categories: Organizations based in RussiaCivil rights organizationsHuman rights organizations based in RussiaPrison-related organizationsRussia stubsHidden categories: Articles containing Russian-language textAll stub articles            
